This paper deals with the problem of learning from imbalanced data, which is a common challenge in machine learning. The proposed method is based on deep learning and involves rectifying the minority class by hard sample mining in the majority class. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
